WEBVTT

00:00.620 --> 00:01.370
Carl?

00:01.777 --> 00:03.256
I heard about the young woman.

00:03.416 --> 00:05.091
Were you able to correct her condition?

00:05.251 --> 00:06.301
Do you know her?

00:06.811 --> 00:08.889
I'd like to be kept up-to-date
on her progress.

00:09.009 --> 00:10.430
Yeah, you and who else?

00:10.590 --> 00:12.474
When did you start working for Roth?

00:16.532 --> 00:17.979
Take your hand off me.

00:18.375 --> 00:20.990
If humans follow the same timeline
as the monkeys,

00:21.110 --> 00:22.692
in a week, possibly two,

00:22.853 --> 00:25.334
Nina may begin to experience
the same violent tendencies.

00:25.454 --> 00:28.216
We need to destroy the stem cells
that activated Nina's Jacobson's organ.

00:28.336 --> 00:31.137
Pressurized oxygen
gets into Bob's brain,

00:31.257 --> 00:32.744
could cause oxidative stress,

00:32.904 --> 00:35.121
that could make the Herpes virus
pop out of the DNA.

00:35.281 --> 00:36.831
We can kill it with the antivirals.

00:36.991 --> 00:37.991
It's gone.

00:39.536 --> 00:40.536
I'm sorry.

00:40.870 --> 00:42.671
Nina's three months pregnant.

00:44.623 --> 00:47.008
When I was a kid, I got sick.

00:48.038 --> 00:48.885
David,

00:49.046 --> 00:50.387
what happened to me...

00:50.961 --> 00:52.011
the baby...

00:53.085 --> 00:54.435
It can't be mine.

01:02.717 --> 01:05.967
When I was nine,
they thought I had testicular cancer.

01:07.129 --> 01:09.229
But what I really had was cysts.

01:10.516 --> 01:12.616
- Okay...
- During the surgery,

01:13.470 --> 01:15.920
they figured out that it wasn't cancer.

01:16.483 --> 01:18.433
But there were complications.

01:18.994 --> 01:19.894
How bad?

01:20.256 --> 01:22.838
My semen contains very few sperm.

01:23.250 --> 01:26.530
I never knew how few
until Dr. Bruen checked.

01:27.846 --> 01:29.134
What was the count?

01:30.362 --> 01:31.112
Zero.

01:32.666 --> 01:34.316
I'm completely sterile.

01:36.409 --> 01:37.684
I'm sorry, Bob.

01:40.083 --> 01:40.983
David...

01:43.782 --> 01:46.232
This pregnancy is very, very confusing.

01:47.129 --> 01:47.879
Here.

01:49.743 --> 01:50.743
Thank you.

01:51.069 --> 01:52.212
You're welcome.

01:52.332 --> 01:53.482
Look, it's...

01:54.663 --> 01:57.163
It's really not that big a mystery, Bob.

01:58.088 --> 02:00.938
I mean, you were gone a long time
and maybe...

02:01.200 --> 02:04.711
Nina probably thought she was never
gonna see you again, she got lonely.

02:05.052 --> 02:07.881
- Along comes another guy...
- She would never cheat on me, David.

02:10.370 --> 02:11.470
Okay then...

02:11.765 --> 02:13.765
Maybe somebody made a mistake.

02:13.885 --> 02:14.971
That happens.

02:15.268 --> 02:18.297
We'll get Carlos to get a genetic sample
of the fetus from Dr. Bruen.

02:18.417 --> 02:20.211
We'll compare it to your DNA.

02:20.547 --> 02:22.745
Find out for sure if you're the father.

02:23.804 --> 02:25.302
The baby is mine.

02:27.692 --> 02:28.942
Of course, Bob.

